Psychiatry in its present form is based on a one-to-one interview that is then written up from the memory of the person who conducted the interview.This leaves a lot of scope for misrepresentation,and hard evidence such as videotape is not used. Nor is there group inter-rater reliability,but instead the creation of a "United Front" of Professional Vanity to prevent criticism.

"On being sane in insane places" Rosenhan; 
"The Psychopath Test" Jon Ronson; 
"The Stanford Prison Experiment" Zimbardo

We propose that legal aid should be provided to all families attending all inquests, with a fairer test on: 

•	Whether an individual is financially eligible, in terms of their disposable income & capital; 

•	Whether other interested persons attending the inquest have legal representation; 

•	The circumstances of the deceased’s death & complexity of the issues.

We submit that the proposed wider scope is fairer & recognises the real need for representation for all families at all inquests.
